<dl id="n12116a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12116a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12116a"> 116(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> rains <font face="wake">A</font>?</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Et, tandis qu&apos;il narrait ainsi les tourments de son &acirc;me d&apos;ap&ocirc;tre, les larmes tombaient de ses yeux, inondant sa lettre. Vainement, il les refoulait: &ldquo; Je voulais s&eacute;cher des pleurs, soupirait-il, et voici que je les provoque;&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[And, as soon as he told in this way of the sufferings of his apostle&apos;s soul, tears fell from his eyes, flooding his letter. Vainly, he stemmed them: &ldquo;I intended to dry away tears&rdquo;, he sighed, &ldquo;and here I am causing them&rdquo;.]</font> <small> <a name="STCM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STCM"><cite title="source">Saint Colomban</cite></a> (1905) 125</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
